{"id": "EUVD-2022-55228", "enisaUuid": "c32cad1c-70c3-3e9c-8904-8823b62dc4a2", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nclk: bcm: rpi: Prevent out-of-bounds access\n\nThe while loop in raspberrypi_discover_clocks() relies on the assumption\nthat the id of the last clock element is zero. Because this data comes\nfrom the Videocore firmware and it doesn't guarantuee such a behavior\nthis could lead to out-of-bounds access. So fix this by providing\na sentinel element.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:36", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-14T21:30:27", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/fcae47b2d23c81603b01f56cf8db63ed64599d34", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ff0b144d4b0a9fbd6efe4d2c0a4b6c9bae2138d2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c8b04b731d43366824841ebdca4ac715f95e0ea4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bc163555603e4ae9c817675ad80d618a4cdbfa2d", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49946"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49946"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1141d134-9abd-37fd-812f-92456d4e1a07", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "93d2725affd65686792f4b57e49ef660f3c8c0f9 <bc163555603e4ae9c817675ad80d618a4cdbfa2d"}, {"id": "1f4dbd14-6108-309d-a65b-d6841e30e60d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.9"}, {"id": "5b0442a5-462a-31ea-9372-b3a2088a5f34", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.66"}, {"id": "77fabcef-8f47-353a-9ce8-d2165b3022d2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "8fb1ee15-c369-3535-b6f2-718c50d75825", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "93d2725affd65686792f4b57e49ef660f3c8c0f9 <ff0b144d4b0a9fbd6efe4d2c0a4b6c9bae2138d2"}, {"id": "96cca8a7-ca81-384c-a41c-681df958a724", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "b612d3bb-84a4-3a4d-b71d-99866ec173a8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.8"}, {"id": "c7